FILE Permissions :-

touch file1.txt

-rw- |r--|r-- . 1  root root 0 
  O  |  G| Ot
  
Here
   O- owner
   G- group
   ot-other
   r= read
   w=write/add/delete/edit
   x=execute/run scripts
   
PERMISSIONS CAN SET BY TWO WAYS:
------------------------------
1)Symbolic method(ugo) :
Here we use 

chmod u=rwx,g=rw,o=rx filename.txt


2)Absolute method :
   Read=4
   write=2
   execute=1
 
 chmod 644 demo.txt
 
*****
UMASK :-
-------
umask=user file creation mask.

The default umask value is 022.

The default permissions for a directory is 755.

The default permissions for a file is 644.

The mechanism inside this default values are umask values.

umask for root is 0022.

we can set umask value by umask 027. For permenant change add these ---> .bashrc, .bash_profile, or .profile for bash

We can create a directory on full permissions by using .

----->mkdir -m 777 directoryname


Troubleshooting 

Q)How th default values are comming ?

The full permissions of a file is = 666
the umask value is                =-022
                                 -------
					Total    =		644	   
                                --------
								
								
The full permissions of a directory is = 777
the umask value is                     =-022
                                       -------
					     Total    =		755   
                                      ---------								
								
								
